(secondQuint)Efficacy and Safety Study of Creon IR in Subjects With Pancreatic Exocrine Insufficiency Due to Cystic Fibrosis.

 This study is a Phase II, randomized, parallel-group, active-controlled, double-blind, dose ranging, multicenter study with 4 different doses of Creon IR and one dose of the active control Creon(R) (DR/GR), administered in subjects of 12 years or older with PEI due to CF.

 The study is divided into two periods: a screening period of 14 days and a double-blind treatment period of 6 to 7 days.

